side dish.'),(512,'en','App\\Entity\\RecipeStep','description','10','Wash the potatoes under running water and cut them into wedges.'),(513,'en','App\\Entity\\RecipeStep','description','11','Heat the oil in a pan and add the potatoes, cumin, marjoram and black pepper. Mix well and cook on medium-low heat for about 20 min, stirring often on order to cook potatoes evenly on all sides.'),(514,'en','App\\Entity\\RecipeStep','description','12','At the end of cooking time add crushed garlic and salt, mix well, and cook for another 5 min. The potatoes should be soft inside and a bit crispy outside.'),(515,'en','App\\Entity\\RecipeStep','description','13','Melt the butter and add it to the flour. Separate yolks from whites and add them to the flour with butter. Set the whites aside.'),(516,'en','App\\Entity\\RecipeStep','description','14','Start to mix all together, gradually adding milk, the pancake mixture should be quite liquid. Whip the whites and add them to the mixture, also add salt to taste, and mix all together.'),(517,'en','App\\Entity\\RecipeStep','description','15','3.Heat the butter in a frying pan, pick some mixture with a ladle and distribute evenly on the pan surface. Cook thin pancakes on both sides, on medium-high heat.'),(518,'en','App\\Entity\\RecipeStep','description','16','Put caviar on a pancake in a line and roll the pancake.'),(519,'en','App\\Entity\\RecipeStep','description','17','Bring water with coarse salt to boil in a pan. Meanwhile, clean turnip greens discarding damaged parts, big leaves stems and end bits of smaller stems. Wash the turnip greens, cut them in pieces about 2 cm big, and throw in the pan with boiling water together with orecchiette. If you use fresh orecchette, add them 5 min after you put in turnip greens. Cook pasta for the time indicated on a package.'),(520,'en','App\\Entity\\RecipeStep','description','18','In the meantime heat some olive oil in a wide frying pan, add chopped garlic and let it brown, then turn off the gas, add anchovies and stir well to let them blend into the rest of the sauce. When orecchiette are done, drain them, putting some liquid aside, and add them to the sauce. Turn on the gas, and stir pasta well for a couple of min on high heat to let it absorb the flavour. In case orecchiette are a bit dry, add a ladle of liquid which you kept aside, turn off the gas, add a little bit of chilli pepper to taste, and stir again. Serve orecchiette with turnip greens immediately while they are still hot.'),(521,'en','App\\Entity\\RecipeStep','description','19','Peel and trim the onions and slice them thinly. In a large saucepan heat a big chunk of butter with a generous drizzle of olive oil, and add the onions with 2 bay leaves. Let them brown, stirring well, for 6 min. Meanwhile boil the water.'),(522,'en','App\\Entity\\RecipeStep','description','20','Sprinkle the flour on the onions and let it toast for 4 min, stirring constantly. Pour boiling water, stir well in order to avoid the lumps to form. Flavour the soup with a generous pinch of salt and let it cook for 40 min. As an option you can enhance the flavour of soup by using vegetable stock instead of just water.'),(523,'en','App\\Entity\\RecipeStep','description','21','Cut emmental in slices of 2-3 mm. Slice the bread and toast it in the oven at 200 for about 5 min, until it gets golden brown.'),(524,'en','App\\Entity\\RecipeStep','description','22','Place bread slices into individual ovenproof soup pots and fill them with soup, after having removed the bay leaves. Add emmental on top and put the pots in the oven at 200 for 3-4 min to let the cheese melt. Serve the onion soup straight in the individual pots.'),(525,'en','App\\Entity\\RecipeStep','description','23','Cleanse the vegetables and chop them up. Heat the oil in a casserole and fry the vegetables on low heat for 10 min, stirring every now an then. Add stock, salt, pepper, cover the casserole and simmer for 40 min.'),(526,'en','App\\Entity\\RecipeStep','description','24','Once cooked, remove the casserole from gas and let the cream cool down, then blend it.'),(527,'en','App\\Entity\\RecipeStep','description','25','Put it again on gas to heat up. Distribute the cream in soup bowls, sprinkle with a bit of chopped parsley and serve.'),(528,'en','App\\Entity\\RecipeStep','description','26','Preheat the oven to 180 C. Wash the aubergines, trim the ends, and scoop out the pulp with a teaspoon, leaving 1 cm thick border, and put the pulp onto a board.'),(529,'en','App\\Entity\\RecipeStep','description','27','Grease a baking tray with 2 tbsp of oil. Brush the inside of aubergines with 2 tbsp of oil, sprinkle some salt and place them on the tray. Cook in the oven for 20 min.'),(530,'en','App\\Entity\\RecipeStep','description','28','Meanwhile cut the salmon in small cubes. Soak the raisins in hot water, then drain and dry them. Chop the pulp of aubergines up with olives and sauée in a frying pan with 2 tbsp of oil and a slightly squashed clove of garlic for 5 min. Add raisins, capers and 2 tbsp of tomato sauce, stir and cook for another 5 min. Eliminate garlic, adjust with salt and pepper to your taste, and take off the heat.'),(531,'en','App\\Entity\\RecipeStep','description','29','Stir salmon into hot sauce and fill aubergines with this mixture. Pour the remaining tomato sauce on a backing tray and flavour it with a remaining clove of garlic, sliced, and the olive oil. Add the aubergines, put them again into the oven and cook for 30 min.'),(532,'en','App\\Entity\\RecipeStep','description','30','Once the cooking time is finished, take the aubergines out of the oven, garnish with fresh basil leaves and serve.'),(533,'en','App\\Entity\\RecipeStep','description','31','In a little bowl put yeast and 2 tsp of sugar, and dissolve in about 20 ml of water. Dissolve fine salt in the rest of warm water, and pour in 40 ml of olive oil.'),(534,'en','App\\Entity\\RecipeStep','description','32','Put flour in a bowl and add the water with yeast and sugar, and the water with salt and oil and knead for about 10 min (or 3-4 min with a food processor), until you obtain smooth dough. Move the dough to a pastry board with a bit of flour and form a ball from it.'),(535,'en','App\\Entity\\RecipeStep','description','33','Pour 40 ml of olive oil onto the centre of a baking tin and put dough on it. Place the baking tin into the oven and leave it to rise for 1.5 hours (the oven should be switched off and closed). Take out the dough, which should have doubled in volume, and start working it with your hands, greased with oil, to prevent sticking, stretching the dough to cover the entire surface of the tin. With your fingertips imprint the signs on the surface to form the classic \"holes\", and let it rise again for 30 min.'),(536,'en','App\\Entity\\RecipeStep','description','34','Sprinkle some coarse salt onto the surface of the dough, and pour the rest 20 ml of oil, to cover the \"holes\". Leave the dough to rise for another 30 min. Meanwhile, chop up rosemary and capers.'),(537,'en','App\\Entity\\RecipeStep','description','35','In the meantime, pre-heat the oven to 200 C. Complete your focaccia with chopped capers and rosemary and also distribute the olives evenly on the surface. Spray some water on the surface and bake the focaccia in the oven for 20 min. When it is ready, take out of the oven and let it cool down before serving.'),(538,'en','App\\Entity\\RecipeStep','description','36','Put water for pasta to boil. Chop up the mushrooms and fry them in olive oil with a clove of crushed garlic for 5 min. Add mackerel, tomato sauce, basil, stir well and let cook for 10 min., stirring every now and again.'),(539,'en','App\\Entity\\RecipeStep','description','37','Cook pasta for the time, indicated on the pack, drain it, and add to the sauce. Mix everything together and stir for a minute in order that pasta absorbs flavour. Your pasta is ready!'),(540,'en','App\\Entity\\RecipeStep','description','38','1.Put oil in a frying pan and fry onion, garlic and parsley until they get a bit of golden colour. Add chopped tomatoes and cook on low heat for 25 min. Add salt and pepper to taste.'),(541,'en','App\\Entity\\RecipeStep','description','39','Cook penne for half time indicated on the package, drain well.'),(542,'en','App\\Entity\\RecipeStep','description','40','Grease the baking tray with oil and put a layer of pasta. Cover with a layer of bacon, a layer of tomato sauce and cheeses. Repeat the procedure until you finish all ingredients, and sprinkle cheese on top.'),(543,'en','App\\Entity\\RecipeStep','description','41','Cook in the oven, preheated to 180 C, for 30 min, or until a golden crust forms on the surface. Serve instantly to the table.'),(544,'en','App\\Entity\\RecipeStep','description','42','Peel and wash the onions. In a casserole melt the butter, gradually adding sugar, and stir well. After 5 min pour balsamic vinegar, stir for a couple of minutes, and then add onions and bay leaves.'),(545,'en','App\\Entity\\RecipeStep','description','43','Cover and let cook for 5 min, then remove the lid, and continue cooking on low heat for about 35 min, stirring from time to time. If necessary, add a ladle of hot water, it will prevent onions from getting dry.'),(546,'en','App\\Entity\\RecipeStep','description','44','Serve small onions in sweet and sour sauce as a starter or as a side dish to meat courses.'),(547,'en','App\\Entity\\RecipeStep','description','45','Wash the shrimp, dry them, make a cut along the back and devein them. Finely chop up an onion.'),(548,'en','App\\Entity\\RecipeStep','description','46','In a frying pan heat 3-4 tbsp of oil and fry the chopped onion for 5 min. Add the shrimp and fry them for a couple of minutes on both sides on high heat, until they become uniformely brown.'),(549,'en','App\\Entity\\RecipeStep','description','47','Drizzle a little bit of white vinegar and soy sauce over the shrimp. Add sugar and ginger and mix well. Let it cook for another 2-3 min on high heat, until the sauce becomes thick and syrupy. Serve the shrimp hot with their sauce, decorating with some fresh parsley.'),(550,'en','App\\Entity\\RecipeStep','description','48','Peel and clean the small onions, eliminating the rootlets and damaged foliar stems. Pour a little oil in a backing dish, add sugar and balsamic vinegar and put on medium fire, let it caramelize for 4-5 min, stirring continuously.'),(551,'en','App\\Entity\\RecipeStep','description','49','Add 2 bay leaves, small onions, boiling stock, adjust with salt and put the backing dish in the oven, preheated to 180 C. Cook for 15 min.'),(552,'en','App\\Entity\\RecipeStep','description','50','Meanwhile, clean well the mushroom caps, eliminating bits of soil with a wet kitchen paper. Add the mushrooms to the onions, mix well and cook in the oven for another 10 min. When this side dish is ready, eliminate the bay leaves, complete with freshly ground black pepper and chopped fresh parsley and serve.'),(553,'en','App\\Entity\\RecipeStep','description','51','Trim the aubergines and cut them in round slices 0,5 cm thick, and grill them for 7-8 min, turning once in the middle of cooking time. Roast the whole peppers in the oven at 200 C for about 10 min., until the skin is darkened and swollen. Peel the peppers, remove the stalk, seeds and filaments and cut them in slices 3-4 cm wide. You can roast the peppers in a different way by holding them over gas, also in this case the skin should become dark and swollen. Once burnt, the skin will come off easily. You can also put them still hot in a paper bag, like a bag for bread, close well and leave there for a little bit before peeling: with the steam forming inside the skin will come off even easier.'),(554,'en','App\\Entity\\RecipeStep','description','52','Mix chopped sage, rosemary and garlic with salt and pepper and use this mixture to flavour the chicken both inside and outside. Wash a lemon well and put it inside the chicken, to give it good flavour and to eliminate fat.'),(555,'en','App\\Entity\\RecipeStep','description','53','Put the chicken in a backing tray and pour some olive oil over it. Cook in the oven at 200 C for 1 hour. The chicken is ready when it is golden-brown and crispy outside and soft inside.'),(556,'en','App\\Entity\\RecipeStep','description','54','Cut it up in quarters or in smaller pieces and serve immediately, garnished with roast potatoes and fresh lettuce.'),(557,'en','App\\Entity\\RecipeStep','description','55','Crush green pepper with prongs of a fork and press it with hands on both sides of each fillet.'),(558,'en','App\\Entity\\RecipeStep','description','56','Put a frying pan with butter and oil on gas, salt the fillets and put them into the pan. Pour cognac in, let it evaporate and then add cream. Let it cook for about 5 min, turning the meat over at least once.'),(559,'en','App\\Entity\\RecipeStep','description','57','In case the sauce is too liquid, remove the fillets from the pan and keep them in a warm place, then turn up the heat and let the sauce reduce. Serve the fillets hot with their sauce and garnish with green beans.'),(560,'en','App\\Entity\\RecipeStep','description','58','Wash the green beans, trim and cook in boiling salted water. When they are cooked al dente, drain them and place in cold water to stop the cooking process.'),(561,'en','App\\Entity\\RecipeStep','description','59','Melt some butter in a pan and add green beans, salt, pepper, and finely chopped parsley. Stir well and leave for a couple of minutes to let the beans absorb the flavour.'),(562,'en','App\\Entity\\RecipeStep','description','60','Remove from gas and sprinkle with a bit of lemon juice, stir again and serve hot.'),(563,'en','App\\Entity\\RecipeStep','description','61','Cut the meat into regular pieces a couple of cm big. Peel an onion and cut it into thin slices. Peel and wash the potatoes and cut them into thin slices as well. Remove cabbage base and core, divide the leaves and wash them well, and cut the thick and hard ribs off.'),(564,'en','App\\Entity\\RecipeStep','description','62','Butter a backing dish well, and place first some leaves of cabbage, then onion slices, a part of pork mix, salt and pepper, some chopped slices of bacon and potatoes. Repeat the procedure, finishing with a layer of cabbage leaves, covering all other ingredients.'),(565,'en','App\\Entity\\RecipeStep','description','63','Cover the backing dish with its lid or with aluminium foil and put in the oven preheated to 150 C for 2 hours. When it is ready, remove from the oven and serve to the table directly in the backing dish.'),(566,'en','App\\Entity\\RecipeStep','description','64','Cut the onions in very thin slices and put them in a bowl. Mix the vegetable oil with vinegar, sugar and salt and pour over the onions, mix well.'),(567,'en','App\\Entity\\RecipeStep','description','65','Marinate the onions for 1 hour, stirring every now and then. Drain the marinade and season with sour cream and chopped fresh parsley.'),(568,'en','App\\Entity\\RecipeStep','description','66','Clean the pepper by eliminating stalk, seeds and filaments, and cut it into 2 cm squares. Peel the cucumber and dice it into 0,5 cm pieces. Eliminate the base, leaves and filaments of celery, and dice it. Also clean the turnip greens by eliminating tough stems and damaged parts. Set aside the \"flowers\" (inflorescences similar to broccoli), and cut the rest in 2 cm pieces.'),(569,'en','App\\Entity\\RecipeStep','description','67','Take a wide pan and fry pepper, celery, cucumber and turnip greens with olive oil on high heat, stirring often. After 3-4 min add salt and pepper, reduce the heat and let cook for another 5 min. At the end add turnip inflorescences, stir well, and after 3 min take off the heat.'),(570,'en','App\\Entity\\RecipeStep','description','68','Meanwhile, prepare couscous, flavour with a little olive oil and distribute it widely on a plate. Place the hot vegetable sauce in the centre of the plate, garnish with pistils of saffron, freshly ground pepper and serve immediately.'),(571,'en','App\\Entity\\RecipeStep','description','69','Rinse moscardini well under running water. Put them in a pan with a generous drizzle of olive oil (4-5 tbsp), 1-2 whole cloves of garlic, slightly crushed, a pinch of chilli pepper, a sprig of wild fennel and enough water to cover the mollusc. Put a lid on, bring to boil on medium heat and let the moscardini stew until almost all liquid is absorbed, about 30 min, and at the end complete with a pinch of salt.'),(572,'en','App\\Entity\\RecipeStep','description','70','When the moscardini are almost done (to check it, prick them with a fork: they should be very soft), let couscous reconstitute and flavour it with a drizzle of olive oil.'),(573,'en','App\\Entity\\RecipeStep','description','71','Spread couscous on the plate and put stewed moscardini with their sauce on top. Garnish with some fresh wild fennel, some olive oil and serve.'),(574,'en','App\\Entity\\RecipeStep','description','72','Peel the potato and cut it into the chunks of 2 cm. Cut the meats into the cunks of the same size. Peel the onion, chop it up finely and fry in a casserole with a drizzle of olive oil for 2-3 min. Add the meat and let it brown on high heat for 4-5 min, stirring often. Season with salt and pepper and pour in a splash of wine. After 1-2 min add a potato and half a cup (about 100 ml) of hot water. Put a lid on, reduce the heat and let it stew for about 20 min.'),(575,'en','App\\Entity\\RecipeStep','description','73','Peel the tomatoes, remove the seeds and cut into big chunks. Cut the aubergine and the courgette in 2 cm big cubes, and also pepper after having removed stalk, seeds and filaments. Fry these vegetables in a pan with olive oil and a lightly crushed clove of garlic on high heat for 5-6 min. Add the vegetables to the meat and cook for another 10 min.'),(576,'en','App\\Entity\\RecipeStep','description','74','Meanwhile lt couscous reconstitute and garnish it with a little olive oil. Season the mix of meat and vegetables with basil leaves, cleaned and torn into smaller pieces. Stir well, adjust with salt and place the mix in the centre of a plate, put couscous around it and serve.'),(577,'en','App\\Entity\\RecipeStep','description','75','Cut the top of the peppers off from the part of the stalk, remove seeds and filaments, sprinkle with salt, turn over and keep on a cutting board (so that they lose vegetation water).'),(578,'en','App\\Entity\\RecipeStep','description','76','Peel the tomatoes and cut them into big chunks. Cut the prawns in 2-3 pieces each and fry them in a pan for 3-4 min with tomatoes, a drizzle of oil, a pinch of salt and freshly ground pepper, stirring often.'),(579,'en','App\\Entity\\RecipeStep','description','77','3.Add couscous and vegetable stock to the pan, stir well, turn off the gas and fill the peppers with this mixture. Put the peppers on a backing tin greased with oil, sprinkle them with some oil and cover with their tops, which you kept aside. Pour a little bit of water into the tin and cook in the oven at 200 C for an hour. When they are done, take out of the oven, garnish with chopped parsley and torn basil leaves and serve.'),(580,'en','App\\Entity\\RecipeStep','description','78','Trim and scrape the carrot and cut it into 1-2 mm stripes. Cut in the same way the pepper after having eliminated seeds and filaments. Cut the cucumber into slices of 2-3 mm (eliminate the central seeds if they are too many). Chop the cauliflower into small florets, and discard the hard stalks.'),(581,'en','App\\Entity\\RecipeStep','description','79','In a wide frying pan heat the oil with a sprig of rosemary, a few chilli rings (remove the seeds if you want it less spicy), and a clove of garlic cut in half (remove it as soon as it gets golden-brown). In this seasoning fry the vegetables (cauliflower, carrot, pepper and cucumber) for 5 min, keeping them separated. Sprinkle with some vinegar and after 2 min add a bit of salt. Turn the gas off and let it cool down.'),(582,'en','App\\Entity\\RecipeStep','description','80','Blend the beans with some oil, parsley, rosemary, salt and pepper to obtain smooth cream.'),(583,'en','App\\Entity\\RecipeStep','description','81','Cut the baguette in 24 slices about one cm thick and toast them in the oven at 200 C for 3-4 min. Cover with the beans cream and garnish with cold vegetables.'),(584,'en','App\\Entity\\RecipeStep','description','82','Soak the beans in cold water for at least 8 hours. Drain them and put in a casserole, cover with plenty of water. Add a peeled onion, 2 whole cloves of garlic, a sprig of sage and 1-2 bay leaves. Cover, bring to a boil on medium heat and cook for an hour. Taste the beans to check whether they are cooked and soft, if not cook for a bit longer.'),(585,'en','App\\Entity\\RecipeStep','description','83','When the beans are cooked, add some coarse salt and after 2 min turn the gas off. Discard the onion, garlic and herbs and drain the beans, keeping the formed stock (there should be about a litre, if it is less then add some boiling water with half of a stock cube dissolved in it).'),(586,'en','App\\Entity\\RecipeStep','description','84','In a different casserole fry the second onion, peeled and chopped, with olive oil, for about 3-4 min. Add the tomatoes, peeled and cut in big chunks, and fry for a couple of minutes. Next add cannellini and their stock, bring to a boil, adjust with salt if necessary, and let it cook for 5 min, turn the gas off. Garnish the soup with a drizzle of raw olive oil, fresh basil leaves, torn with hands into small pieces, and freshly ground pepper. Serve canellini beans and tomato soup hot.'),(587,'en','App\\Entity\\RecipeStep','description','85','In a bowl combine flour, milk and yeast and form thick batter, then let it rise in a warm place. Add melted butter, eggs, salt, mix well and let it rise again.'),(588,'en','App\\Entity\\RecipeStep','description','86','Melt some butter in a frying pan on medium-high fire, take the batter with a ladle and form small thick pancakes (3 pancakes in a 24 cm frying pan). Fry for about 3 min until the bottom side becomes golden-brown, then turn over and fry for another 2 min.'),(589,'en','App\\Entity\\RecipeStep','description','87','Place ready pankaces on a plate in a pile, putting a bit of butter between them, complete with sour cream on top and serve while still hot.'),(590,'en','App\\Entity\\RecipeStep','description','88','Wash anchovies under running water to remove salt and cut them into small pieces. Bring the butter to room temperature. Chop up the parsley finely.'),(591,'en','App\\Entity\\RecipeStep','description','89','In a mortar and pestle combine all ingredients and grind them into a smooth paste. Transfer the paste on a plate and give it a desired shape with a wet knife. You can serve it as a spread on toast, with the pancakes or with the boiled potatoes.'),(592,'en','App\\Entity\\RecipeStep','description','90','Prepare hard-boiled eggs, peel and let them cool down. Cut each egg lengthwise and cut a little bit of the convex part off in order that the halves don\'t fall.'),(593,'en','App\\Entity\\RecipeStep','description','91','Put caviar on yalks, place the halves of the eggs on a plate and decorate with fresh parskey. '),(594,'en','App\\Entity\\RecipeStep','description','92','Wash the anchovies, discard the head, open them and remove the fishbones, then wash the fillets and dry them. Cover the bottom of a glass or steel tray with vinegar, put the fillets in one near another, add a little bit of salt, pour the rest of vinegar, cover with the plastic wrap and leave it to marinate in the fridge for 24 hours.'),(595,'en','App\\Entity\\RecipeStep','description','93','Chop up the parsley with garlic and chilli pepper, put the mixture in a bowl, add salt, pepper and oil and mix well.'),(596,'en','App\\Entity\\RecipeStep','description','94','Drain the anchovies from the marinade and place them in layers into a glass container, covering every layer with the prepaired sauce. Close the container and put it into the fridge for 2-3 hours before serving. These anchovies can be kept in the fridge for about a week, make sure that they are completely covered with sauce, add more oil if necessary.'),(597,'en','App\\Entity\\RecipeStep','description','95','Soak the beans for 6-8 hours, then drain them and rinse well. Put the beans in a pan filled with water and boil on high heat for 15 min, then reduce the heat and simmer for 45 min.'),(598,'en','App\\Entity\\RecipeStep','description','96','Take the beans off the heat, drain and rinse again, discard the water. Put them in a pan and add boiling water. Now it is time to add other ingredients: vegetable stock, potatoes, coriander and fenugreek seeds, chilli powder, tomato concentrate. Mix well and leave to cook for about 2 hours, stirring every now and again. Long cooking time will ensure softness not only of the beans but also of the skins, and will also make the stock dense and creamy.'),(599,'en','App\\Entity\\RecipeStep','description','97','When the beans are about ready, chop up an onion, a clove of garlic, and parsley and fry them in oil until onion is golden brown. Add this mixture to the bean stew, cook for another 5 min and take off the heat. Your bean stew with potatoes is ready! '),(600,'en','App\\Entity\\RecipeStep','description','98','First of all wash and peel the potatoes, cut them in pieces and boil for about 20 min. Meanwhile clean the spinach, cut them in pieces and boil them in salty water for 5 min.'),(601,'en','App\\Entity\\RecipeStep','description','99','Drain the potatoes and put them in a bowl. Drain well the spinach, try to eliminate as much water as you can, and add it to the bowl with the potatoes.'),(602,'en','App\\Entity\\RecipeStep','description','100','Chop up the onion and dice carrots and potatoes. Chop up the cabbage, put it in a colander and wash under the running water.'),(603,'en','App\\Entity\\RecipeStep','description','101','Put the onion in a pan and fry it on medium heat for 5 min. Add all other vegetables, pour in boiling stock, add tomato concentrate and seasoning. Cover, bring to boil, then reduce the heat and leave to simmer for about 40 min.'),(604,'en','App\\Entity\\RecipeStep','description','102','Once the soup is ready, distribute it into the warm bowls and sprinkle with some chopped parsley. Serve this delicious soup with country-style bread.'),(605,'en','App\\Entity\\RecipeStep','description','103','In a small bowl combine all ingredients for the marinade and rub it onto the pork ribs on all sides. Place the pork ribs in a backing dish, cover with plastic wrap and let them marinade in the fridge for 2 hours.'),(606,'en','App\\Entity\\RecipeStep','description','104','Take the ribs out of the fridge. Pre-heat the oven to 180 C. Sprinkle with a bit of olive oil and cook in the oven for about 2 hours, turning the ribs over from time to time. Serve with roast potatoes and carrots and green salad.'),(607,'en','App\\Entity\\Recipe','country','7','FR'),(608,'en','App\\Entity\\RecipeImage','label','1','Onion Soup'),(609,'en','App\\Entity\\Recipe','country','9','IT'),(610,'en','App\\Entity\\RecipeIngredient','readableString','54','4 round aubergines'),(611,'en','App\\Entity\\RecipeImage','label','2','Stuffed Aubergines'),(612,'en','App\\Entity\\Recipe','country','1','CN'),(613,'en','App\\Entity\\RecipeImage','label','3','Mushroom Soup'),(614,'en','App\\Entity\\Recipe','country','26','IT'),(615,'en','App\\Entity\\RecipeImage','label','4','Fancy Crostoni'),(616,'en','App\\Entity\\Recipe','country','6','IT'),(617,'en','App\\Entity\\RecipeImage','label','5','Orecchiette');
